<HEAD>ADVERTISEMENT.</HEAD>
<P>THE candour of the public is reque&s;ted for <HI>Tabitha,</HI> who ju&s;t after her 8th &s;quabble, on the 23d of May (whea &s;he was &s;ad|ly drub'd) advertis'd that there were a&s;&s;embled in this city, the la&s;t week, twenty or thirty clergymen, to write again&s;t whigs; make bi&s;hops, &amp;c. But being out of breath, &s;he omitted to in|form the public, that among the degrees confer'd that day, after much debate about a degree of infamy, &s;uitable for Dr. Chauncey, <HI>Tabitha</HI> propo&s;ed the degree of <HI>Ram-chicken,</HI> which was highly approv'd of, and accordingly confer'd.</P>
<P>On <HI>Tabitha Kettle,</HI> for eminent &s;ervices, the name and title of <HI>Tim. Tickle,</HI> <ABBR><HI>E&s;q</HI></ABBR> and that &s;he a&s;&s;ume virility.</P>
<P>As <HI>Tabitha</HI> has already &s;o lavi&s;h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d all the opprobrious names out of Hudibra&s;s, that none are left for W. Living&s;ton and the Whig, &s;he is required to have one again&s;t our next convention.</P>
